Jules,

What Karl said!  (Thank you, Karl and Richard. I looked for that picture
but could not find it.)  As further elucidation, here is what I wrote to
Mr. Finnell earlier today:

> If you look in the base of the dist drive dog and the top of the drive
> gear in the engine you will see a hole in each about 4-5 mm in diameter.
> the spring sits in these holes.  It looks a lot like a spring from a
> ball point pen on serious steroids (~4mm diameter coil and ~2cm long).

OOK!

On Thu, 4 Aug 2005, Karl wrote:

> The key word above is 'between'.
> Between the drive gear and the distributor shaft.
>
> The drive gear is in the case and is turned by the crank.
> The dist shaft is in the distributor and the dog on the bottom is driven by
> the drive gear. 'between' is on top of the drive gear and below the dog.
> #9 here: http://www.ratwell.com/technical/Microfiche/t200400.gif
